items.text: Friendly staff, cozy place for a good breakfast out of the buzz of the city
Enjoy hearty brunches with a view of the stables and grazing horses over the vast spread of green grass. If you have room for dessert, end your meal with their famous chocolate cake.
Prepare to wait a long time for your food
Everything..
Tranquil rustic place for brunch. Always come early to watch the horses. Service could be improved n place air conditioned..
The portobello mushroom / halloumi cheese burger is delicious. The mushroom can often be too thick - this was just right and garnishing was perfect.
Salted caramel brioche with caramel sauce & topped with honeycomb only for those with extreme sweet tooth. Too unbalanced - needs to tone down the cloying sweetness
The Smoked Bacon with poached eggs meal is a must try!
Request for a strawberry banana shake instead of the chocolate one.. It's more refreshing! 
Toilets are air-conditioned. 😳
Try the boston ice tea for a refreshing drink in our summer heat! Topped with tons of berries!
Excellent Brunch
Sherperds pie, riders burger, the usual, cream of potato&scallion;, butterscotch banana pudding, death by chocolate
Death by Chocolate. It's the way to go.
Nice place for breakfast n brunch...
Nice tables by the balcony, but beware of mozzies
Egg Benedicts are good, try the swimmer crab one. Scones are average so does the coffee. Remember to make reservation when u come down on weekend. The waiting time could be 1 hour plus.
Death by Choc is damn good!!!
Hate the smell........
The brioche french toast and usual English breakfast with poached egg are must tries!
Super brunch options :) try the poached egg options and also corn polenta
Make a reservation on their website http://www.riderscafe.sg/ using chope. Works well!
This was a surprise. Nice atmosphere in a nice environment! A cafe at Bukit Timah Saddle Club. Seem to be popular amongst non horse people as well!
Great view but rather hard chairs and limited breakfast selection for a son seeking steak :)
chocolate cake? to die for.
Sunrise smoothie or their cream corn polenta.
Death by Chocolate is indeed yummy. Try the Soft Shell Crab Benedict.
Horse riding on sunday mornings (till 1pm) in front of the door... perfect for the kids...
Pacific eggs Benedict is goood ;) fresh combination of crabs and poached eggs.
The burger is HUGE!
Nice Place for breakfast
The death by chocolate cake is awesome!!! MUST TRY!!
Death by chocolate is a must - just make sure you share it with someone else because it's a big portion.
They have managed to maintain the quality of food here over the years. The scones were a little dry but tasty. Try the brioche french toast for brunch. Yummy.
Limited selection ... coffee so so ...
Roast portobello club is lovely! Tough to get compliment from a die-hard carnivore like me! If you ever have a chance, try their duck leg confit. Most tender inside with a crunchy skin. Best so far
I'd rather the place remain unairconditioned! Feels unlike singapore. What a gem.
Nice place for having calm and quite brunch! Really love it!!
Try the death by chocolate cake!!!!
Make a reservation on the weekends, otherwise it'll be a long wait! Call 6466 9819, they only accept advanced booking and not on the day itself though! :)
CLOSED FOR RENOVATIONS!! REOPEN ONLY IN AUGUST 2013!
Spaghetti aglio olio 😋👍
Grilled octopus was good.
Choc cake is a must! Till Death do Us part!
The place to 'died from chocolate'...death by chocolate!
Charmant petit café. Réservation à l'avance nécessaire.
Nice ambiemce but amateur burger and coffee.
Thank you to all the staffs here for keeping my umbrella.
Great buffalo wings. Crab au vin pasta is good too. Service is a bit patchy tho and leaves alot of room for improvements.
Delicious & substantial cauliflower salad. The snapper as a main was gr8 and watermelon salad w snapper light & tasty. Overall excellent service & coming back for brunch aft our gd lunch experience
On the balcony. Serene country-like facade in front and vibrant cafe city folk chatter. You, across the table. My the thoughts there thereafter are almost as sinful as this chocolate cake we share.
Good food but watch out for the smell of the horses nearby.
eat death by choc only if your friends love choco. Eating alone is simply too much... (:
Had the Brioche French Toast with Bacon & Bananas. Nothing to rave about it. French toast was soggy and rather tasteless. I quite liked the caramelised bananas tho.
Good place to relax but service was way too slow. Had to wait for a long time for the food which wasn't rave-worthy.
Having breakfast ....

items.firstName: ผู้บริสุทธิ์

items.text: Great Breakfast!
Still same old rustic good food.. Bangers are good
Roasted pork knuckle - nicely done!
Nice food, very tasty 😋 don't feel like being in Singapore. Had the steak with beans and egg
Perfect breakfast place on a weekend morning!
Nice environment but menu is weak, specially the breakfast options. Coffee wasn't fresh and extremely bitter. The fries were cold and the burger's bread was covered with blood.
Must try the lamb and banoffee... Oo I love them.. Guess what is banoffee:)
Brioche French toast is awesome! Love the cinnamon smelllllll .... and the chocolate cake is so sinfullllllll!
Staff will kill me but, there is a staff toilet around the back past the gate.
Horses! Nice and Cosy, do note it's open air.
Hv brunch here.. Rider burger is good.
French toast is pretty good although a bit sickening after a while. Coffee is average. Nice place but not spectacular
The Breakfast Burrito is huge. Easily enough for two with an extra side or two. If you have kids then book way way ahead and ask for a table one balcony so you have a view over the stables.
Service so slow! Disappointing!
Good piccolo latte. Great atmosphere - it's like being in the countryside far far away from Singapore!
Like the environment lots!
Closed on Mondays
Love their vanilla ice cream on theor death by chocolate cake!! The cake is fairly big sized and definitely too much even for 2!
Order their poached eggs with crab cakes and smoke salmon set. Try to avoid going during summer period as it is not air conditioned and some may not be used to the strong stench from outside.
Really good food, reasonable price. Love "the usuals" breakfast.
Brunch is till 11am only!
Love their pumpkin and crab soup!
Great place for weekend breakfast with the family!
Everything on the menu is good! You won't be disappointed. :) [although i did find the prices for the kids menu a little on the high side!]
